@startuml Three-Layer Architecture
!theme plain
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam packageFontSize 14
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF

title POS System Three-Layer Architecture

package "UI Layer" as UILayer #LightBlue {
  note right
    <b>Responsibilities:</b>
    - User interaction
    - Input validation
    - Data display
    - Call service layer
    
    <b>Modules:</b>
    - POSUI (CLI)
    - POSGUI (GUI)
  end note
}

package "Service Layer" as ServiceLayer #LightGreen {
  note right
    <b>Responsibilities:</b>
    - Business rule processing
    - Process control
    - Transaction management
    - Coordinate domain models
    
    <b>Modules:</b>
    - InventoryService
    - SaleService
    - ReturnService
  end note
}

package "Domain Layer" as DomainLayer #LightYellow {
  note right
    <b>Responsibilities:</b>
    - Business entity definition
    - Business concept modeling
    - Data encapsulation
    - Business rule expression
    
    <b>Modules:</b>
    - Transaction (abstract)
    - Sale
    - ReturnTransaction
    - Product
    - SaleItem
  end note
}

UILayer --> ServiceLayer : calls
ServiceLayer --> DomainLayer : uses

note bottom
  <b>Layered Architecture Principles:</b>
  1. Upper layers can depend on lower layers
  2. Lower layers cannot depend on upper layers
  3. Layers at the same level can have dependencies
  4. Each layer focuses only on its own responsibilities
end note

@enduml
